Author: EidooTeam
Title: [ANN] | EDO |EIDOO Wallet - Hybrid Exchange - Marketplace| OVER 80k ETH RAISED |
Body: Our partnerships with Binance and Bitfinex regarding IEO's in the past were punctual, depending on the IEO's offered. If you hold BNB in your Eidoo Wallet, it is the old ERC20 token, and we would suggest you swap it to the new BEP2 token by simply sending it to your Binance account. Also, please note that at the moment you can't participate on Binance launchpad if you hold BNB tokens in your Eidoo wallet. (It is good idea thou)  Quote from: magisterr on August 10, 2019, 07:26:43 AM How many tokens are you going to burn automatically? For what period of time this buren will be? Every month or every quarter? What do you mean partnered? Will you have own IEOs like this has other exchanges? On our Edo token page, https://eidoo.io/edo-token you can follow all the burn transactions, and in the Details section, you can see what EDO is and will be used for, and also how much will be burned from it. At the moment we burn 50% of the EDO we gain as trading fees on our Hybrid Exchange (also from swaps), and we check for these every two hours, and 50% of all Eidoo Crowd platform fees. We have no burn period, as long as EDO will be paid as fee we will burn a % from it. We have and will have IEO/IDO's offered on our Hybrid exchange, and also we have Eidoo Crowd, https://crowd.eidoo.io/app/, as our ICO/STO platform.

Title: [ANN] | EDO |EIDOO Wallet - Hybrid Exchange - Marketplace| OVER 80k ETH RAISED |
Body: Eidoo is and is not just another wallet. Our hybrid exchange, where most pairs don't require KYC, is up and running: https://eidoo.io/hybrid-crypto-exchange. If you do our KYC, Eidoo ID, you will be able to buy Crypto with Wire Transfer and also participate in our IEO's. We also have Simplex integrated to help you buy Crypto with your Credit card. Next step is to integrate our IEO/STO platform, https://crowd.eidoo.io/app/, inside our Eidoo app. At the moment we only support BTC, ETH and it's ERC20/ERC223 tokens, but the support of more blockchains is coming, we are working on that.  We are also working on many other cool and interesting features so stick around, follow us on Telegram, https://t.me/eidoocryptochannel, Twitter: https://twitter.com/eidoo_io, Reddit: https://www.reddit.com/r/eidooapp/.

Author: EidooTeam
Title: [ANN] | EDO |EIDOO Wallet - Hybrid Exchange - Marketplace| OVER 80k ETH RAISED |
Body: Eidoo v2.0.x is out!!!  A new version of the Eidoo App is live - an all-around platform to access and manage cryptocurrencies from zero to hero. For those who have not poked around with the app recently, below is a sneak peek of what you can find there: - super easy #Swipe2Swap feature, enabling users to purchase or exchange crypto assets with just a swipe. The blockchain industry is a rollercoaster and Eidoo arms you with the tools you need to enjoy the ride; - Improved version of the Bitcoin wallet, providing a unique place where to manage all crypto assets; - Exclusive access to unique opportunities such as Bitfinex’s LEO token and other Binance and Bitfinex-backed IEOs; - New feature to access digital assets via credit card and wire transfer. A simple gateway to the cryptocurrencies world for those who are new to it; - Support for multiple stablecoins backed by different underlying assets (USDT, Moneyfold’s fiat-backed tokens, Ekon’s gold-backed tokens) to enable portfolio diversification; - Improved version of the app - faster and more fluid! Including faster app launch, improved push notifications handling, new exchange descriptions and more.  Whether you are a hodler or a trader, Eidoo is there for you.  An all-around platform providing all the tools you need to enjoy the crypto rollercoaster as a pro!  More is coming. Shh, don’t tell anyone!

This is to offer a store of value and to beat the value fluctuations of cryptocurrencies.  Ekon Gold is a physical gold bars-backed cryptocurrency developed by Eidoo, a Swiss-based company that runs a hybrid exchange and cryptocurrency wallet for bitcoin (BTC), ethereum (ETH) and all tokens based on the Ethereum blockchain (ERC20 and ERC231).  Ekon.Gold is an ERC20 token that is equivalent to 1 gram (999) of fine gold. It is stored in a certified and insured Vault in Switzerland....

Author: Nikolas.Glushe
Title: [ANN] | EDO |EIDOO Wallet - Hybrid Exchange - Marketplace| OVER 80k ETH RAISED |
Body: Dear Eidoo community. We are pleased to inform you about our project https://echats.top/ which logs all important telegram chats related to Eidoo. We believe that Eidoo Chats will be a valuable addition to the Eidoo ecosystem. During the work of the site, we have already received a large number of positive feedback from community members. The project is under active development. The project has its own team of programmers, ready at any time to solve new technical problems and make new improvements.  What is implemented at the moment: You can read your favorite sites in a convenient form for you through https://echats.top/ The site is optimized for work and on mobile devices. There is a search by keyword and date. It is possible to read the chat you want in your native language using Google Translate. The translation is not perfect, but it will allow you to receive the latest news as quickly as possible from the first sources.  In the near future, we plan to add the ability to share a specific telegram post in social networks. On the one hand, this will allow you to share interesting content with your friends and subscribers, and on the other hand, it will positively influence the development of Eidoo ’s popularity in general.  There is a lot of work ahead, we have planned a huge number of interesting and useful improvements. If you have any suggestions for improving our site, please write - we will try to take everything into account and use it in the further development of the site.  If you think that some important chat related to Eidoo is missing on our website, please write and we will add it.

Body: If the project will be realized as the roadmap I am also convinced that Edo can become among the top coin at the market, but a tip: do not leave too many coins on your phone because the phones by definition are not safe.   Quote from: lite on July 16, 2018, 02:34:32 PM I just downloaded eidoo exchange preview app to test it and couldn't test it, it's asking me to complete identity verification? do i really have to do verification to use the exchange?  Exactly, to use the decentralized hybrid exchange, as well as to have the debit card, which will be launched shortly, and many other services, you must have a Tier2 verification on the site https://www.icoengine.net/ it will take a few days, and then you will also have a privileged access to Ico on the Eidoo platform, without going through the numerous frequent whitelists. Author: kronos123
Title: [ANN] | EDO |EIDOO Wallet - Hybrid Exchange - Marketplace| OVER 80k ETH RAISED |
Body: Experts in computer security say that to have the maximum security the PC must always be off-line .... once you connect to the internet it is compromised; then if we add that 99% of users use the PC to register at each site that meets, go on facebook or telegramm, there are those who go on auction sites or porn, then it is almost certain risk hacking. The smartphone is VERY WORSE! because every app you download from android or IoS asks to access your address book, messages, camera and much more, before being installed; moreover, almost all of them connect to public wi-fi without vpn or protections, download everything they read, etc. Trust me: do not keep a lot of coins on your smartphone!     So without that verification there's no way i can use the exchange? that's not how a decentralized exchange should operate. If eidoo doesn't allow use of exchange without doing verification then i think it'll have hard time getting users.  Exactly, without verification you can not operate on the Eidoo exchange (it is hybrid, not decentralized), just as you can not make the debit card request, or use the marketplace (Q3-Q4), or participate in the ICO reserved for a value beyond 3000 Swiss francs. All this is required by FINMA, which is the Federal Financial Supervision Authority of Switzerland. Greater severity = greater security. Similar to the FSA of Japan  Quote from: mandibleclaw on July 17, 2018, 05:38:54 PM The debit card request will be free or it will costs a fixed amount of EDO (or eth ? or fiat?)? I read the whitepaper a long time ago and I don't remember (or maybe it wasn't even written in the whitepaper?)  It will be free but will be given priority over its ordering and shipping to the holders of Eidoo, from pre-ico to ICO, and then to those who bought in exchanges. The taxes and costs of the debit card will be paid in Edo and a part of them will be burned, thus reducing the supply.

Body: To tell the truth, I`ve found some activity from Eidoo team in July, but it was not related to new the dates of Roadmap at all. But at least I found that it may be interesting for the community to read as we have no many to choose from.  Found the article in www.express.co.uk about Bitcoin price and among others, there was a short interview with Thomas Bertani, Director of Eidoo.  Reiterating comments made earlier this year, Mr Bertani said: "We are in the middle of an extremely interesting hype cycle where the price fluctuations mirror the construction of a totally new market with its huge possibilities coupled with uncertainty about the unknown.  "I believe bitcoin is in a much needed 'rest' phase so that smart companies are able to make the changes and provisions needed to tackle the overhaul that's coming from regulation and institutional investments entering the market.  "The price will then once again soar."  Source - https://www.express.co.uk/finance/city/979066/Bitcoin-price-ripple-cryptocurrency-ethereum-BTC-to-USD-XRP-news

Title: [ANN] | EDO |EIDOO Wallet - Hybrid Exchange - Marketplace| OVER 80k ETH RAISED |
Body: To all who's curious about the EIDOO Bitcoin app, it is not a separate wallet, but it is in Beta as of the moment. You need to confirm for Beta testing to be able to try it. So here's how:  [1] Go to Google Play Store [2] Search for Eidoo and go to app detail page [3] Scroll the page to the bottom, you'll see the "Become a beta tester" there, click I'M IN             [4] You need to confirm that you want to "Join beta program", click JOIN             [5] Just wait for a few minutes for the UPDATE button to show up             [6] Once finished, click UPDATE             [7] SUCCESS! You are a beta tester already, OPEN the app to check             [8] Yahoo! Bitcoin is now available :   Helpful Source on how to Get beta versions of apps : https://support.google.com/googleplay/answer/7003180?hl=en

Body: June will be decisive. The beginning was good, but then the project almost stopped. Author: holydarkness
Title: [ANN] | EDO |EIDOO Wallet - Hybrid Exchange - Marketplace| OVER 80k ETH RAISED |
Body: By "EIDO token", do you mean EDO or the general ERC-20 tokens that you store on EIDOO?  For the former, according to their telegram, and I believe it should be mentioned somewhere on this thread, EDO will be used for transaction on their exchange. Means, the advantage of keeping your EDO on your app is... well, you need them in their soon-to-come exchange.  If you mean the later, I personally think there is no significant difference between storing thr ERC-20 on mew or eidoo aside from eidoo give an easier access if you want to move your token to exchange, as mew will likely needs you to access your computer. But if they launched their exchange, then storing on eidoo will give an obvious advantage of easy access to the market that can't be provided by mew.

Author: jasomantr
Title: [ANN] | EDO |EIDOO Wallet - Hybrid Exchange - Marketplace| OVER 80k ETH RAISED |
Body: Hey guys.. Dont be funny. Today we learnt that EDO has frozen 6million tokens and released them in an unknown period of time. Just as you guys, we were suspecting who was selling EDO from 2900-3000 sats.. Then we thought it might be EDO itself founders. We decided to follow up Circulating Supply and Total Supply through Coinmarketcap. (because it would rise if founders etc were selling) Circulating supply was around 20M as usual.. We didnt check last 10-15 days.  Today we noticed that Circulating Supply is now 29M.  Then we asked how and when it happened at EDO Official Telegram Channel. They said that, "Old circulating supply on coinmarketcap was wrong. It was about 24 Millions EDO. Then at the beginning of January was unlocked 6 Millions EDO (as you can read in the whitepaper). Last week it was updated on coinmarketcap"  Here is the proof of what they said; https://pbs.twimg.com/media/DU4EU_LWkAAmmII.jpg:large  So guys, they have embedded this information into hidden corner of Whitepaper and Medium Blog. They didnt mention on Twitter, Telegram, Facebook or Coinmarketcalendar.  Do you now understand why we couldnt break that 5000 satoshi wall ? Yea, that was him ! It was impossible to break 6 million tokens wall. Do you now understand who is selling tokens from 2900-3500 satoshi ? Thats him again. How to sell from 2900-3500 satoshi man? how much did you buy this huh ? While its ICO  was $2.8  They even blocked us on twitter just bcs we asked questions..  So.. decision is up to you ! Thx

Author: ortim
Title: [ANN] | EDO |EIDOO Wallet - Hybrid Exchange - Marketplace| OVER 80k ETH RAISED |
Body: what i really like about the wallet is that it recognizes even new tokens correctly and does not require any manual adding of "costum tokens". Great interface and easy to use  Presently it's my preferred hot wallet. I never invested in EDO, but maybe i will.   Only thing i don't like about the wallet is that a simple password is enough to make a transaction. So if someone hacks your mobile phone, your money is lost (same problem with most phone wallets). Would be nice to have some kind of 2 factor security check.

Author: Ginzink
Title: [ANN] | EDO |EIDOO Wallet - Hybrid Exchange - Marketplace| OVER 80k ETH RAISED |
Body: The password is only as simple as you make it I feel much more safe using Eidoo than mew, but 2 factor could be nice. But as Eidoo cannot help you if the two factor is lost for some reason and the 2-factor is usually your phone i dont see a good usecase for it apart from an unnecesary step complicating the use of wallet?  Of course you could use a 2 factor which itself was locked with a password on the phone. It would be for the more advanced user with alot of funds locked it. But i think thoose guys would just have the backup key and not have it installed all the time. Just guessing here but interesting discussion to be had maybe?

Author: Nadia_l
Title: [ANN] | EDO |EIDOO Wallet - Hybrid Exchange - Marketplace| OVER 80k ETH RAISED |
Body: Good news never come alone)  Eidoo announces the AidCoin Pre-sale — CharityStars to use the Eidoo ICO Engine  Eidoo and CharityStars are announcing an agreement that will consist in the use of the Eidoo’s recently revealed ICO Engine, which AidCoin will use to launch its AID token pre-sale. AidCoin (AID) is the token for charitable giving, built on the Ethereum Blockchain and empowered by CharityStars.  AidCoin will use Eidoo wallet, to perform the AID pre-sale on November 20th, 2017 to provide more security for the pre-sale participants and enabling a smooth user experience without the need for technical knowledge.  This pre-sale is exclusive for Eidoo, meaning that users can join the AidCoin pre-sale only through the Eidoo mobile app.  It was published on Eidoos official medium page some hours before - https://medium.com/eidoo/eidoo-announces-the-aidcoin-pre-sale-charitystars-to-use-the-eidoo-ico-engine-8d9b0aa0df47  And there also will be airdrop organized by CharityStars) A total of 125 000 AID tokens will be distributed accordingly to active Eidoo wallet users! This airdrop is going to be launched on November 19th for all the Eidoo active users.  So, who is still not active Eidoo wallet user don`t delay)

Author: xiao2017
Title: [ANN] | EDO |EIDOO Wallet - Hybrid Exchange - Marketplace| OVER 80k ETH RAISED |
Body: I like that!  2018 is year for EIDOO   The Eidoo Brand The Eidoo most prominent goal is to have a worldwide adoption. This means that we need a robust branding to be recognizable and have a consistent theme because we want to establish a significant and differentiated presence in the market to attract and retain loyal supporters like you. To do so, we are working on our branding, improving our logo, app design, colors, and more.  ICO Engine On Friday, we launched a new service called “ICO Engine” to help new startups in organizing their token sales through our mobile app available for both iOS and Android. This tool has already been used by us to organize our successful token sale a few months ago.  The main advantage regarding the use of our ICO Engine is security, as Eidoo has a reliable system that ensures the safety of the funding avoiding the risk of assets loss that might be due to computer hacking or scams. In fact, we want to provide a safe tool that guarantees that the ICO address is always the same so that funds arrive at the startup correctly. Another advantage is that Eidoo has high visibility, thanks to our 130k downloads and, because of that, we have a massive potential for airdrops that are becoming a useful for new tokens for creating a significant advertising effect for users who recognize receiving a gift that has a quantifiable value.  To better advertise and explain this new tool we have also created a new section of the site that you can visit here.  ERC20 Tokens List A few days ago, we updated our official website adding a new page called “Supported Tokens,” as you can read in the top right menu. This page contains a vast ERC20 tokens list. Eidoo, in fact, supports all the ERC20 and ERC223 tokens, so you can use our wallet to store these Ethereum-based tokens.  This ERC20 tokens list has been filled automatically with all the tokens included in Coinmarketcap, so it is almost complete, but it might happen that some tokens may be missing, especially if they have an ongoing ICO or pre-sale.

"Eidoo tokens will be erased by one half and the other half resold to cover the operational costs. Then the token will initially serve to make cash. When the exchange starts, some operations can only be done with tokens. When you do an operation, half of the used tokens will be burned while the other half will be used to cover the costs. If you keep the tokens in fact you do not go to burn the tokens while the others who will use the exchange will. This will actually increase the price-to-token in the long run.

Author: HenkdPee
Title: [ANN] | EDO |EIDOO Wallet - Hybrid Exchange - Marketplace| OVER 80k ETH RAISED |
Body: How is this EDO token gaining value? This ICO is only about the release of a multi-cryptocurrency wallet with an integrated Exchange (for ETH tokens). So, not very different from WAVES with their embedded DEX exchange in their wallet (website and soon mobile. Waves app with exchange is currently in pilot).  So, I guess the value of the EDO is determined basis the usage of the integrated Exchange. Probably, EDO has to be paid (as a fee) for every transaction made on the integrated exchange.  I understand the money-making (EDO coin value) concept but how is it different from WAVES? And, why is the start-price for the token so incredible expensive? 130 tokens for 1 ETH?! Today, that's around $2.15 per EDO coin! Why is that? Today the coin is of zero value, not being used and the multi-cryptocurrency wallet with an integrated Exchange has not even proven itself today. I believe $0.01 per EDO coin would have been more appropiated.  Anyways, just my view. I wish Eidoo and its investors all the success of the world.
